<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Tasks — {{FEATURE_TITLE}}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="spec.css">
</head>
<body>
<div class="page-wrap">

  <nav class="sidebar" aria-label="Table of contents">
    <p class="sidebar-title">Contents</p>
    <div id="toc-list"></div>
  </nav>

  <div class="main-content">
    <header class="spec-header">
      <h1>Implementation tasks — {{FEATURE_TITLE}}</h1>
      <table class="meta-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Task ID</th>      <td><code>{{TASK_ID}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Feature slug</th> <td><code>{{FEATURE_SLUG}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Status</th>       <td><span class="badge badge-draft">spec_draft</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </header>

    <main>

      <section id="tasks">
        <h2>Tasks</h2>
        <p>Implement tasks in the order listed. Each task should be small and independently verifiable.
           Mark a task complete by adding <code>class="done"</code> to its <code>&lt;li class="task-item"&gt;</code>
           (<code>in-progress</code> and <code>blocked</code> are also available). The global task status lives in <code>tasks.json</code>.</p>

        <ol class="task-timeline">
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T1</span>
              <strong>TODO: Add or update tests for requirement <code>REQ-001</code>.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Write or update automated tests before implementing to confirm the requirement is currently failing.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T2</span>
              <strong>TODO: Implement the smallest code change needed for <code>REQ-001</code>.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Keep changes focused. Do not expand scope beyond the approved spec.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T3</span>
              <strong>TODO: Add edge-case handling.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Cover the edge cases identified in <code>requirements.html</code>.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T4</span>
              <strong>TODO: Run validation commands.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Run tests, lint, and typecheck as configured in <code>CLAUDE.md</code>.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T5</span>
              <strong>TODO: Update documentation if needed.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Update any user-facing docs or changelog entries that cover this change.</div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <!-- OPTIONAL CLOSING TASKS — include only the ones that apply to this
             feature (the design's Documentation targets, Project map references,
             Security and permissions, and UI sections say which). Do not add
             them to simple tasks they do not apply to.

          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T?</span>
              <strong>Update affected documentation.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Update the targets listed in the design's <code>Documentation targets</code>; the reviewer confirms in the <code>Documentation decision</code>.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T?</span>
              <strong>Update the project map.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Refresh the map areas this change made stale (new directories, moved entrypoints, changed commands, new protected areas).</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T?</span>
              <strong>Propose decision-log entries.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Draft entries for the significant decisions this task settled (see requirements' <code>Memory and decision implications</code>); propose only — never write without developer approval.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T?</span>
              <strong>Run UI QA.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Verify the UI acceptance criteria via the <code>ui-qa</code> skill / <code>browser-tester</code> agent; record results in the review's <code>Visual verification</code>.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-item-header">
              <span class="req-id t">T?</span>
              <strong>Run the dependency freshness check.</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="task-item-body">Verify current docs for the external systems listed in the design's <code>External dependencies and freshness</code> and record the evidence there.</div>
          </li>
        -->
      </section>

      <section id="validation-checklist">
        <h2>Validation checklist</h2>
        <p>The reviewer verifies each item below before marking the task <code>done</code>.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Requirements are covered by tests.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Tests pass.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Lint / typecheck pass if configured.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> No protected files were modified without approval.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Reviewer approved traceability.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Documentation decision recorded (required with targets, or not required).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div><!-- /.main-content -->
</div><!-- /.page-wrap -->
<script src="spec.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
